-- Dubai to spend up to $5.1 billion on MGM stake
-- 
-- Wed Aug 22, 2007 8:31am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/22/us-mgm-dubai-purchase-idUSL2283711520070822

 

 DUBAI  (Reuters) - Dubai said on Wednesday it agreed to pay as much as $5.1 billion for a 9.5 percent stake in MGM Mirage Inc ( MGM.N ), and half of the casino company's CitiCenter hotels and apartments project in Las Vegas. 

 State-owned Dubai World said it will buy 14.2 million MGM shares from the company at $84 each and 14.2 million shares from investors at the same price. It will also pay $2.7 billion for half of CityCenter, Dubai World said.